Fix permission rule tool-name case to match the registry

`mvp_tool_specs` (`tools/lib.rs:388`) registers the bash tool as
lowercase `"bash"`. `PermissionRule::matches` (`permissions.rs:378`)
performs exact string equality on tool names. Patch 0001 used capital
`"Bash"` in deny and ask rules — these never match a real `bash`
invocation, so the hardened config silently does nothing.

The capital-B form was copied from upstream's `ROADMAP.md` examples,
which appear to be aspirational documentation rather than the actual
runtime convention. Switch to lowercase `bash` to match the registry.

Discovered while probing the harness against a local Ollama model on
2026-04-24: a `bash` tool call with `ls -la` ran without triggering
the `ask: ["Bash"]` catch-all that was supposed to surface every Bash
invocation for confirmation.

Note: this patch only fixes the rule-name match. It does NOT explain
why a `bash` call (which requires `DangerFullAccess`) ran while the
active mode is `default` (= ReadOnly). That's a separate trace —
likely the `claw prompt` subcommand resolves to a more permissive mode
than `.claw.json` declares. Verify by testing with a deny rule that
*should* now fire (e.g. `bash(sudo:*)`) after applying this patch.
---
diff --git a/.claude.json b/.claude.json
--- a/.claude.json
+++ b/.claude.json
@@ -2,12 +2,12 @@
   "permissions": {
     "defaultMode": "default",
     "deny": [
-      "Bash(curl:*)",
-      "Bash(wget:*)",
-      "Bash(sudo:*)",
-      "Bash(rm:*)"
+      "bash(curl:*)",
+      "bash(wget:*)",
+      "bash(sudo:*)",
+      "bash(rm:*)"
     ],
     "ask": [
-      "Bash"
+      "bash"
     ]
   }
 }
diff --git a/rust/.claw.json b/rust/.claw.json
--- a/rust/.claw.json
+++ b/rust/.claw.json
@@ -2,12 +2,12 @@
   "permissions": {
     "defaultMode": "default",
     "deny": [
-      "Bash(curl:*)",
-      "Bash(wget:*)",
-      "Bash(sudo:*)",
-      "Bash(rm:*)"
+      "bash(curl:*)",
+      "bash(wget:*)",
+      "bash(sudo:*)",
+      "bash(rm:*)"
     ],
     "ask": [
-      "Bash"
+      "bash"
     ]
   }
 }
